rs that approach this topic from a variety of perspectives, and they provide a vital new tool for understanding how welfare states operate.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Aug 2021) 0aWelfare statexEconomic aspectszEuropean Union countries. 0aWelfare statezEuropean Union countries. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aAchterberg, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAchterberg, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aDekker, Fabian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDérogée, Pascal, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeilbron, Johan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMascini, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPruijt, Hans, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aQuak, Sander, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRaven, Judith, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSoentken, Menno, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTijdens, Kea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVeen, Romke van der, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYerkes, Mara, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYerkes, Mara, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 avan der Veen, Romke, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backfile 2000-2013z978311070067140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048515318zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048515318423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/97